    "description": "Case sensitivity flag logic is inverted in createRegExp. The 'i' (case-insensitive) regex flag should be added when matchCase is FALSE (case-insensitive search), but the code adds it when matchCase is TRUE. This breaks all case-sensitive/insensitive search operations across find-and-replace, bracket matching, and search workers.",
