    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Position.isBefore boundary condition is wrong. The docstring states 'If the two positions are equal, the result will be false', but the code returns true when positions are equal because it uses `<=` instead of `<`. This violates the contract and breaks all code that depends on strict ordering semantics for cursor movement, undo/redo, and position comparisons.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/src/vs/editor/common/core/position.ts
+++ b/src/vs/editor/common/core/position.ts
@@ -100,7 +100,7 @@ export class Position {
