    "file": "src/vs/editor/common/core/range.ts",
    "line": 97,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "Range.containsPosition boundary condition is inconsistent. The code uses `>=` to exclude the end position, making the range exclusive at the end boundary. However, the docstring says 'If the position is at the edges, will return true', and the parallel containsRange method uses `>` (not `>=`) for the same semantic check, treating the end boundary as inclusive. This causes decorations, selections, find-and-replace highlighting, and code lens to incorrectly exclude end positions.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/src/vs/editor/common/core/range.ts
+++ b/src/vs/editor/common/core/range.ts
@@ -94,7 +94,7 @@ export class Range {
 		if (position.lineNumber === range.startLineNumber && position.column < range.startColumn) {
 			return false;
 		}
-		if (position.lineNumber === range.endLineNumber && position.column >= range.endColumn) {
+		if (position.lineNumber === range.endLineNumber && position.column > range.endColumn) {
 			return false;
 		}
 		return true;
"
  },
